recentchanges aka Developer buddy

recentchanges. aka Developer buddy      recentchanges / recentchanges search
Provide ease of pattern finding ie what files to block we can do this a number of ways
1) if a file was there (many as in more than a few) and another search lists them as deleted its either a sys file or not but unwanted nontheless
2) Is a system file inherent to the specifc platform
3) intangibles ie trashed items that may pop up infrequently and are not known about

Modes available Search Query See bottom after usage how to use modes


recentchanges s         where s is time in seconds	output AppData

usage:    recentchanges		system search 5 minutes or new these will include system search as well
usage:    recentchanges 30		system search 30 seconds or newer


Modes

Search        for just a system search	output Desktop

recentchanges search	search for files 5 minutes or newer
recentchanges search 30		search for files 30 seconds or newer

Search for files newer than a file or directory

recentchanges search /home/guest/myfile.txt    search for files newer than myfile
recentchanges search myfile.txt
recentchanges search /home/guest/My\ Directory\ two/with\ spaces/   ... newer than directory


Query

Find out information about files from searches.

Inverse the search with Symlink

rnt.bat	shortcut for recentchanges
rnt n			doesnt inverse output AppData
rnt search		search for filtered rather than unfiltered files	output Desktop
rnt search 30		search for filtered files 30 seconds or newer
rnt search myfile.txt	search for unfiltered rather than filtered files newer than myfile


If having problems with keys.
1. Try to delete the all .gpg to make new ones. 2. Failing that do the same as 1 but change email in config.toml to make a new keypair

or option 3.
use recentchanges reset. to delete the key pair and gpgs and reset

